rnal callers can’t conveniently name.\n\n   Minimal fix: either re-export it from `lib.rs`, or better, if we do item 1, rename it to a CLI-only `TargetKind` and re-export it only if needed. Since `Command` is already public for `but`, I’d re-export the type if it remains in the variant.\n\nTiny non-issue: the clones/ownership look fine. `target_key: String` and `Vec<RelatedSession>` are owned because the command output owns them; `join(\",\")` is display-only and harmless.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:01:51.212Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}